<item>
            <title>[HBASE-5354] Source to standalone deployment script</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-5354</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Automating the testing of source code in a &apos;real&apos; instance can be a bit of a pain, even getting it into standalone mode.&lt;br/&gt;
Steps you need to go through:&lt;br/&gt;
1) Build the project&lt;br/&gt;
2) Copy it to the deployment directory&lt;br/&gt;
3) Shutdown the current cluster (if it is running)&lt;br/&gt;
4) Untar the tar&lt;br/&gt;
5) Update the configs to point to a local data cluster&lt;br/&gt;
6) Startup the new deployment&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yeah, its not super difficult, but it would be nice to just have a script to make it button push easy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
